        <p id="_Providing_Experiences_Cyndi_spent_a_lot_of_time_planning_even">
        <span id="textspana7">Providing Experiences<br /></span><span id="textspana8"><br /></span><span id="textspana9">Cyndi spent a lot of time planning events and doing things with the kids. Whether it was picking weeds with our neighbors on Monday night for Family Home Evening or a 4000 mile trip through Utah, Nevada and California, we took time to provide these kind of family experiences together. We did some crazy, crazy things that I don’t think other people would do with a family our size. Now when we get together with the kids, those experiences and vacations are what we talk about.<br /><br />We always made a point to go. It was always a sacrifice, because we didn’t have a lot of money and we just prayed the car would get us there. Sometimes it failed us, but most the time it came through. Those are the experiences we wanted to preserve. Again, was it a sacrifice? It might have looked like a sacrifice then, but when you look back, each one of them has turned into a blessing. Hopefully we’ve passed that legacy onto our kids. If they want to have family experiences with their children that teach them to get off the couch and do things, to be outdoors in nature, to hike, to get involved, they know it's possible.</span><br />
        </p>
        <p id="“Is_it_a_sacrifice_It_might_have_looked_like_a_sacrifice_then_">
        “Is it a sacrifice? It might have looked like a sacrifice then, but when you look back, each one of them has turned into a blessing.”
        </p>
