        <p id="I_think_the_experiences_were_important_because_it_got_Cyndi_out">
        I think the experiences were important because it got Cyndi out of the house. She needed breaks. I don’t know if going on vacation was really a vacation for her because it took far more work, but it was a break of sorts because it was a different type of work. Same with me; it was a different type of work. Certainly we didn’t go do romantic things with 7-8 kids in tow. We did things that kids wanted to do like camp on the beach, hunt for rocks, make sand castles, hike along shore lines, etc.It was important for us to get the children out and enjoying nature, seeing the world, seeing the ocean. We lived 5-6 hours aways from the ocean, so whenever we went it was special. We would spend at least several days at the beach enjoying the waves and ocean, even as cold as it was. Was it worth it? Worth every minute and every dime we spent.
        </p>
